l justice; women as sheriffs; and a Nottinghamshire study examining the tensions between the role of the king as manorial lord and as monarch. Contributors: NICK BARRATT, PAUL R. BRAND, DAVID CARPENTER, DAVID CROOK, ANTHONY MUSSON, NICHOLAS C. VINCENT, LOUISE WILKINSON  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 4aMedieval History. 7aHISTORY / Medieval.2bisacsh  aBureaucracy.  aEnglish Government.  aLaw and Justice.  aLocalities.  aMedieval Society.  aRoyal Government.  aThirteenth Century.1 aBarratt, Nick, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBrand, Paul A, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBrand, Paul, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCarpenter, David X., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCarpenter, David, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCrook, David, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJobson, Adrian L, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aMusson, Anthony, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aVincent, Nicholas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWilkinson, Louise J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBoydell and Brewer Complete eBook-Package pre 2013z978311143139040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781846152337?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781846152337423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781846152337/original  a978-3-11-143139-0  Boydell and Brewer Complete eBook-Package pre 2013b2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles